{"legislative_session": "20252026", "identifier": "AB1908", "title": "Civil actions: victims' compensation funding: validating proceedings.", "from_organization": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["bill"], "subject": ["Civilactions", "validatingproceedings", "victims'compensationfunding"], "abstracts": [{"note": "summary", "abstract": "Under existing law, bonds, warrants, contracts, obligations, and evidences of indebtedness of a public agency, for the purpose of validating proceedings, are deemed to be in existence upon their authorization, as specified.\n\nThis bill would provide that the obligations described above include a victims' compensation fund, established to address payments to settle or pay awards to victims of childhood sexual assault, as specified, which is authorized as of the date the establishment of such a fund via adoption of a resolution or ordinance by a county board of supervisors. The bill would provide that, for purposes of determining the validity of refunding bonds to refund a tort action judgment entered against a public agency, as specified, indebtedness is deemed to be in existence on the date of adoption by the governing body of the public agency of a resolution ordinance, as specified. The bill would provide that whether a tort action judgment or settlement or a victims' compensation fund is deemed to be in existence is not contingent on the timing of the commencement of a tort action, the court's issuance of a judgment, the entry into a settlement, or the victims' compensation fund's claim period."}], "other_titles": [{"note": "", "title": "Civil actions: statute of limitations."}], "other_identifiers": [{"identifier": "ocd-bill-ca-20252026-ab1908"}], "actions": [{"description": "Read first time. To print.", "date": "2026-02-12", "organization_id": "~{\"classification\": \"lower\"}", "classification": ["reading-1"], "related_entities": []}, {"description": "From printer. May be heard in committee March 15.", "dat